cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses extensions to traditional logic programming. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as inductions and game semantics are commonly used in AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes an execution model for a logic language. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) may be relevant as the paper discusses capturing a wider class of provable formulas. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may be relevant as the paper proposes a new execution model.
